TALENT MANAGER (Seattle + New York)

ROLE

Reporting to CTO, the Talent Manager will lead all activities related to the Human Resources function of Sid Lee Seattle-NY. Combining both strategic and HR-operational responsibilities, it will need to evaluate, improve and evolve the company's talent management and HR activities as well as offer support to the team regarding complex issues. The Talent Management Manager works closely with senior management to align HR strategies with those of the company.

TASKS
Partner with Business leaders and provide thought leadership, using quantitative skills and knowledge of the agency and the external marketplace to evaluate the impact of HR/Talent activities on organizational performance for both the Seattle and New York offices;
Provide coaching and play an advisory role to the leadership team on how to manage and resolve complex HR issues;
Drive change and implement processes that increases retention, engagement and productivity;
Design, develop and deliver tailored-talent strategies and talent governance to support the Seattle/New York offices in the achievement of their strategic objectives;
Accountable for the organizational development activities including talent development, leadership development, cultural change, employee engagement, etc.;
Lead the HR cycle activities with the leadership team and relevant stakeholders;
Manage total rewards offering, by not only ensuring the administration but the value add of base pay/variable pay, benefits, work life, career development, employee recognition;
Advise leaders on how to maximize talent by defining current and future talent needs and ways to develop their teams to address performance and capability gaps;
Partner with the recruiting team to ensure a positive and seamless candidate experience and strategic future focused hiring;
Collaborate closely with the Global Talent Management Team to accomplish global projects by identifying and clarifying issues and priorities; communicating and coordinating requirements; designing/developing/deploying projects; evaluating milestones, changing assumptions and direction, as required;
Participate in the implementation of the new HRIS system, and leverage the system to drive operational efficiency;
Contribute, with a continuous improvement mindset, to the implementation of a best in class global Talent function;
Promote a culture of feedback and open communication, reinforcing the agency's values.
SKILLS
Above average leadership orientation, ownership and accountability;
Result-oriented with collaborative approach to accomplishing goals;
Ability to manage several projects simultaneously
Strong relationship-building skills with the ability to influence up, down and across the organization
Track record of success in the development and delivery of complex HR programs, strategies, and processes
Well-developed critical thinking and analytical abilities;
Strong desire to continuously learn, grow and develop others and excellent coaching skills;
High level of communication skills and comfortable with open communication and constructive feedback.
REQUIREMENTS
University Degree in Human Resources Management or Organizational Development;
Minimum of 7 to 9 years of experience in a high speed/high growth environment;
Experience managing direct reports;
Demonstrated experience in managing, designing, developing and deploying HR processes and leadership programs;
Experience in Advertising, Media, Entertainment or other creative industries, an asset;
Excellent communication skills, both written and oral, in English.
